math>,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"y equals 35\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>35</mn></math>. Substituting these values into the given equation yields <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"7 left parenthesis 8 right parenthesis minus 4 left parenthesis 35 right parenthesis equals negative 84\"><mn>7</mn><mo>(</mo><mn>8</mn><mo>)</mo><mo>\u2212</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>(</mo><mn>35</mn><mo>)</mo><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>84</mn></math>, or&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"negative 84 equals negative 84\"><mo>\u2212</mo><mn>84</mn><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>84</mn></math>, which is true. Therefore, the table in choice A gives three values of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x\"><mi>x</mi></math> and their corresponding values of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"y\"><mi>y</mi></math>.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Choice B is incorrect. The table in choice B shows that when <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x equals 0\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math>, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"y equals 35\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>35</mn></math>. Substituting these values into the given equation yields <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"7 left parenthesis 0 right parenthesis minus 4 left parenthesis 35 right parenthesis equals negative 84\"><mn>7</mn><mo>(</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>)</mo><mo>\u2212</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>(</mo><mn>35</mn><mo>)</mo><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>84</mn></math>, or&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"negative 140 equals negative 84\"><mo>\u2212</mo><mn>140</mn><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>84</mn></math>, which is not true.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Choice C is incorrect. The table in choice C shows that&nbsp;when <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x equals 21\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn